The z command supplements the p command, to enhance the playing of
audio data. The command may be preceded by a block address where play
is to begin. If omitted, play resumes where it left off. The z may be
followed by a span of time to be played in seconds, with a default of
five seconds. Omitting this value causes the previous span to be used.
Thus, to play audio in chunks of ten seconds, beginning with block 11,
you would first type 11z10 and press enter. To read subsequent ten second
chunks, type z, press enter, type z, press enter, etc. If a block is
longer than 1000 milliseconds, i.e. one second, the span value is the
number of blocks instead of the number of seconds.

